description.narrative: The office has further strengthened its internal management and oversight capacity to effectively manage partnership ensuring transfer of knowledge and capacities to CSOs particularly to local entities. Investments have been made to ensure transparency in selection and assessments of partners’ proposals under the principles of intersectionality, access and concentration of responsibilities rather than number of beneficiaries. With a heavy reliance of the programme on partner’s implementation, the intent has been to ensure that CSO’ actively participate in the design, planning and localization of UNCEF’s high level impact and are not the mere recipients of funding that produces outcome-related activities. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:19/01/2022
